article.description: — Maxwell Land scored 26 points as Saint Francis (PA) beat Hartford 77-53 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Land puts up 26, Saint Francis (PA) downs Hartford 77-53
article.linkText: Land puts up 26, Saint Francis (PA) downs Hartford 77-53
article.story: LORETTO, Pa. -- — Maxwell Land scored 26 points as Saint Francis (PA) beat Hartford 77-53 on Saturday night. Land was 11-of-18 shooting (2 for 5 from distance) for the Red Flash (1-1). Landon Moore scored 14 points while going 6 of 13 (2 for 8 from distance), and added six rebounds and six assists. Josh Cohen was 4-of-5 shooting and 3 of 4 from the free-throw line to finish with 11 points. The Hawks (1-2) were led by Pano Pavlidis, who recorded 13 points and nine rebounds. Jared Kimbrough added 11 points and six rebounds for Hartford. In addition, Briggs McClain finished with 11 points. NEXT UP Saint Francis (PA)'s next game is Monday against Cornell at home. Hartford visits Boston University on Thursday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
